Package com.cafean.client.ui

Class GenericTableDialog.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.ui.GenericTableDialog.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    GenericTableDialog
    public static class GenericTableDialog.Builder
extends java.lang.Object
    This builder is used to build an instance of the GenericTableDialog. This builder provides the following configuration options: 
     GenericTableModel configuration:
    addColumn
 
     Table Cell Editor/Renderer configuration:
    addEditor
    addRenderer
 
     Column Header Tooltip configuration:
    addColumnHeaderTooltip
 
     Toolbar configuration:
    setAddButtonAction
    setRemoveButtonAction
    setMoveUpButtonAction
    setMoveDownButtonAction

    Note that if no action for a particular button is provided it will be
    omitted. If no actions for any of the toolbar buttons are provided
    the toolbar in its entirety will be omitted.
 
     Error Label configuration:
    setErrorSupplier
    An example of using the builder follows: 
       GenericTableDialog.Builder builder = GenericTableDialog.builder(parent, model, clone::getCells);
   builder.addColumn(column1(clone));
   builder.addColumn(column2(clone));
   builder.addColumn(column3(clone));
   builder.setAddButtonAction(tableModel -> addButtonAction(tableModel, clone));
   builder.setRemoveButtonAction(tableModel -> removeButtonAction(tableModel, clone));
   builder.setMoveUpButtonAction(tableModel -> moveUpButtonAction(tableModel, clone));
   builder.setMoveDownButtonAction(tableModel -> moveDownButtonAction(tableModel, clone));
   builder.setErrorSupplier(this::getCellsErrorMessage);
   return builder.get();
    And an example for building table columns: 
     // Index column
 var indexCol = new GenericTMColumn(i -> i+1, // row function accessor - just the row index + 1
                                    null,  // row function setter - none since you can't set the index by typing in a value
                                    "Index", // Display name
                                    Integer.class, // column class
                                    false); // column is disabled, you can't set the index by typing in a value

 // Cell Initial Conditions:
 // Builds a column for the 'pressure' property of a HydroIC subblock
 var cell = findCell();
 var pressureColumn = new GenericTMColumn(row -> getICs(row, cell), // row function accessor
                                          HydroIC.class, // column class
                                          "pressure", // property name on subblock
                                          row -> getICs(row, cell).isPressureEnabled(), // enabling function accessor
                                          HydroICContext.PRESSURE); // context type
    See Also:
    GenericTMColumn

      • setErrorSupplier

        public void setErrorSupplier​(java.util.function.Supplier<java.util.Optional<java.lang.String>> errorSupplier)
        Registers the Supplier that is queried for an error state whenever a table model event is fired within the dialog. When the given Supplier returns a non-empty Optional, the given string will be displayed in red text at the bottom of the dialog.
        Parameters:
        errorSupplier - a Supplier that provides an Optional with an error string, or empty Optional if no error is applicable.
